The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Four killed in mishaps
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Four killed in mishaps
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Four men were killed in two bus mishaps in the city and its suburbs on Friday.         
	Three men were killed and 14 injured when a speeding private bus overturned while overtaking a truck at Kalikapur on Taki Road on Friday morning. Kartick Roy, 63, and Laksman Mondal, 22, residents of Maslandapur, and Shantanu Dutta, 28, were killed in the mishap. The driver of the bus fled. Residents of the area broke the rear of the bus to rescue trapped passengers.        
	In the other mishap, an unidentified man in his mid-30s died after he fell down while getting off a private bus on APC Road on Friday morning. The driver of the bus fled.        
	Five held: Five persons were arrested in Beleghata on Friday in connection with a two-wheeler theft racket. Police said 11 motorcycles were recovered from the five.         
	Fee protest: Around 150 parents of students of South End School in Kudghat demonstrated outside the campus on Friday morning demanding reduction in fees. The principal did not meet the protesters.         
	Tourist handed over: David Pitman, the 20-year-old German tourist, who was drugged and robbed aboard a train from Beneras to Howrah, was released from hospital and handed over to German consulate officials on Friday. The stolen items have not been traced.                                                                                                                                                          
